s the campsite for dinner and overnight. This small park (at 392 sq km) is the second most popular park in Kenya after Masai Mara, mainly due to the spectacular backdrop of Mt. Kilimanjaro on the southern boundary.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-item\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: none; margin-bottom: 20px; border-radius: 8px;\">\r\n<div id=\"acc-item-2043628199-headingOne\" class=\"accordion-header\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><a class=\"accordion-button\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #313041; appearance: button; position: relative; display: flex; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; width: 733.344px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; font-size: 18px; background: none; border-width: 1px 1px 0px; border-image: initial; border-radius: 8px 8px 0px 0px; overflow-anchor: none; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; box-shadow: none; cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; border-color: #ebe6de #ebe6de initial #ebe6de; border-style: solid solid initial solid;\" type=\"button\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#acc-item-2043628199-collapseOne\" aria-expanded=\"true\" aria-controls=\"panelsStayOpen-collapseOne\">Day 2 &ndash; Amboseli National park</a></div>\r\n<div id=\"acc-item-2043628199-collapseOne\" class=\"accordion-collapse collapse show\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-width: 0px 1px 1px; border-color: #ebe6de; border-image: initial; border-radius: 0px 0px 8px 8px; border-style: initial solid solid solid;\" aria-labelledby=\"acc-item-2043628199-headingOne\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-body\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px 30px 6px;\">the day is spent exploring this park. The waters from melted snow drain down the mountain under lava flows and surface on the Amboseli plains, creating a green belt of swampland amidst dusty plains. Here elephant, buffalo, lion, cheetah, wildebeest, hyena, jackal, warthogs, zebra and the Maasai giraffe are likely to be seen. Amboseli National park is one of the most popular wildlife sanctuaries in Kenya. It is situated close to Kenya. It is situated close to Kenya- Tanzania border, The Park lies at the foot of Mt. Kilimanjaro, the highest mountain in Africa (5,896m) whose snow-capped summit presents a splendid view on clear days. Amboseli National Park is often referred to as &ldquo;The home of Elephants&rsquo; some of the largest Elephant herds are found here. The Game Park also contains vast groups of Zebras, Wildebeests, Giraffes, Buffalos, Hippos and Antelopes. Also to be found in Amboseli are lions, leopards, Cheetahs, Rhinos and many species of plain game.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-item\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: none; margin-bottom: 20px; border-radius: 8px;\">\r\n<div id=\"acc-item-311046231-headingOne\" class=\"accordion-header\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><a class=\"accordion-button\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #313041; appearance: button; position: relative; display: flex; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; width: 733.344px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; font-size: 18px; background: none; border-width: 1px 1px 0px; border-image: initial; border-radius: 8px 8px 0px 0px; overflow-anchor: none; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; box-shadow: none; cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; border-color: #ebe6de #ebe6de initial #ebe6de; border-style: solid solid initial solid;\" type=\"button\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#acc-item-311046231-collapseOne\" aria-expanded=\"true\" aria-controls=\"panelsStayOpen-collapseOne\">Day 3 Amboseli &ndash; Tsavo West National park</a></div>\r\n<div id=\"acc-item-311046231-collapseOne\" class=\"accordion-collapse collapse show\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-width: 0px 1px 1px; border-color: #ebe6de; border-image: initial; border-radius: 0px 0px 8px 8px; border-style: initial solid solid solid;\" aria-labelledby=\"acc-item-311046231-headingOne\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-body\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px 30px 6px;\">After an early breakfast depart for Tsavo West National Park which lies roughly half way between Nairobi and the Coast. Mzima Springs, the chief marvel here is a favorite haunt of hippos and crocodiles. Picnic lunch then proceed for an evening game drive to see large herds of elephants, buffalo, common waterbuck, eland, rhino and a wide variety of antelope. Dinner and overnight at a Camp/lodge</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-item\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: none; margin-bottom: 20px; border-radius: 8px;\">\r\n<div id=\"acc-item-2002356991-headingOne\" class=\"accordion-header\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><a class=\"accordion-button\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #313041; appearance: button; position: relative; display: flex; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; width: 733.344px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; font-size: 18px; background: none; border-width: 1px 1px 0px; border-image: initial; border-radius: 8px 8px 0px 0px; overflow-anchor: none; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; box-shadow: none; cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; border-color: #ebe6de #ebe6de initial #ebe6de; border-style: solid solid initial solid;\" type=\"button\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#acc-item-2002356991-collapseOne\" aria-expanded=\"true\" aria-controls=\"panelsStayOpen-collapseOne\">Day 4: Tsavo West &ndash; Tsavo East National park</a></div>\r\n<div id=\"acc-item-2002356991-collapseOne\" class=\"accordion-collapse collapse show\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-width: 0px 1px 1px; border-color: #ebe6de; border-image: initial; border-radius: 0px 0px 8px 8px; border-style: initial solid solid solid;\" aria-labelledby=\"acc-item-2002356991-headingOne\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-body\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px 30px 6px;\">We break the camp soon after breakfast and proceed to Tsavo East National park. Game is viewed as we exit the park. This park was famed for its large herds of elephant covered in red dust and fine scenery. We visit the scenic Lugards Falls, Mudanda Rocks (attracts elephants in the drier season) and Aruba Dam as we view game if time permits. Dinner and overnight stay at a Camp/lodge</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-item\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: none; margin-bottom: 20px; border-radius: 8px;\">\r\n<div id=\"acc-item-4269306996-headingOne\" class=\"accordion-header\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><a class=\"accordion-button\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #313041; appearance: button; position: relative; display: flex; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; width: 733.344px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; font-size: 18px; background: none; border-width: 1px 1px 0px; border-image: initial; border-radius: 8px 8px 0px 0px; overflow-anchor: none; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; box-shadow: none; cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; border-color: #ebe6de #ebe6de initial #ebe6de; border-style: solid solid initial solid;\" type=\"button\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#acc-item-4269306996-collapseOne\" aria-expanded=\"true\" aria-controls=\"panelsStayOpen-collapseOne\">Day 5: Tsavo East National park</a></div>\r\n<div id=\"acc-item-4269306996-collapseOne\" class=\"accordion-collapse collapse show\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-width: 0px 1px 1px; border-color: #ebe6de; border-image: initial; border-radius: 0px 0px 8px 8px; border-style: initial solid solid solid;\" aria-labelledby=\"acc-item-4269306996-headingOne\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-body\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px 30px 6px;\">Full day spent exploring the park. Morning and afternoon game drives are offered. Dinner and overnight stay at a campsite. The landscape in Tsavo East is flatter and drier, despite having one of Kenya&rsquo;s largest rivers flowing through the middle. Much of the wildlife is concentrated on the Galana River, which has plentiful crocs and hippos. Likewise, Kudus, waterbucks and dik-diks are common along the river banks. The landscape in Tsavo East is flatter and drier, despite having one of Kenya&rsquo;s largest rivers flowing through the middle. Much of the wildlife is concentrated on the Galana River, which has plentiful crocs and hippos. Likewise, Kudus, waterbucks and dik-diks are common along the river banks.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"accordion-item\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: none; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">\r\n<div id=\"acc-item-882946504-headingOne\" class=\"accordion-header\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><a class=\"accordion-button\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #313041; appearance: button; position: relative; display: flex; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; width: 733.344px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; font-size: 18px; background: none; border-width: 1px 1px 0px; border-image: initial; border-radius: 8px 8px 0px 0px; overflow-anchor: none; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; box-shadow: none; cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; border-color: #ebe6de #ebe6de initial #ebe6de; border-style: solid solid initial solid;\" type=\"button\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#acc-item-882946504-collapseOne\" aria-expanded=\"true\" aria-controls=\"panelsStayOpen-collapseOne\">Day 6: Tsavo East &ndash;Mombasa</a></div>\r\n<div id=\"acc-item-882946504-collapseOne\" class=\"accordion-collapse collapse show\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-radius: 0px 0px 8px 8px; border-width: 0px 1px 1px; border-color: #ebe6de; border-image: initial; border-style: initial solid solid solid;\" aria-labelledby=\"acc-item-882946504-headingOne\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-body\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px 30px 6px;\">Early morning game drive. Soon after breakfast we proceed to Mombasa arriving at 1400 hrs.Drop off at a beach hotel to s